Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.53,0:00:14.31,OPR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}kono sora no kagayaki kimi no mune ni todoiteru
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.53,0:00:14.31,OPE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}The luminance of the sky has reached your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.52,0:00:24.34,OPR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}yumemiteta shirabe wa shizukesa no youni
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.52,0:00:24.34,OPE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}The melody I dreamed of was like silence.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:24.21,0:00:29.39,OPR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}kimi no te ga mada yume ni tookutemo
Dialogue: 1,0:00:24.21,0:00:29.39,OPE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}Even if your hand is still far away in my dreams,
Dialogue: 2,0:00:29.23,0:00:34.45,OPR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}omoidashiteyou yasashii koe wo
Dialogue: 2,0:00:29.23,0:00:34.45,OPE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}I’ll still remember your kind voice
Dialogue: 3,0:00:34.21,0:00:47.24,OPR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}dareka ga kimi no tame utatta shiawase no koto
Dialogue: 3,0:00:34.21,0:00:47.24,OPE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}and the happiness that was sung for you.
Dialogue: 4,0:00:46.98,0:00:56.64,OPR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}sora no woto hibike takaku kanashimi wo koete
Dialogue: 4,0:00:46.98,0:00:56.64,OPE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}Let the sound of the sky ring high over your sadness.
Dialogue: 5,0:00:56.41,0:01:07.19,OPR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}kimi no me ni utsuru mono wa subete hontou no sekai
Dialogue: 5,0:00:56.41,0:01:07.19,OPE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}Everything reflected in your eyes is that of the real world.
Dialogue: 6,0:01:07.02,0:01:16.66,OPR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}namida sae kimi wo koko ni todomete okenai
Dialogue: 6,0:01:07.02,0:01:16.66,OPE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}Even tears won’t be able to stop you here.
Dialogue: 7,0:01:16.39,0:01:28.79,OPR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}furisosogu hikari no naka ashita wo kanadete
Dialogue: 7,0:01:16.39,0:01:28.79,OPE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,300)}Amidst the descending lights, you’ll play the song of tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.35,0:01:45.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rio-senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.47,0:01:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good work!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.08,0:01:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The parts?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.85,0:01:52.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We found them without any problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.62,0:01:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They can be found if you just look for them!{You just have to search for it?}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.41,0:01:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so warm!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.83,0:02:01.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alive again...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.70,0:02:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? But Rio-senpai, were you supposed to be on yard duty?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.62,0:02:10.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was something I wanted to burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.66,0:02:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been half a year since Kanata came to the fort, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.88,0:02:30.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astonishingly, she's actually gotten better at playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.16,0:02:32.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's because her teacher is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.20,0:02:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.17,0:02:41.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's finally gotten to the point where we don't need earplugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.89,0:02:49.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Madam. Wouldn't it be better to go into the town this winter after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.35,0:02:52.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.39,0:02:57.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't kick the bucket so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.82,0:03:05.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been living alone on this mountain for 50 years after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.06,0:03:10.06,Titles,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(424,94.666667)}{Title}Setting off
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.06,0:03:10.06,Titles,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(424,421.333333)}Time of the First Snow
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.61,0:03:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. All right. All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.17,0:03:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.46,0:03:19.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's finally coming along.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.26,0:03:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noël, will you be fine on your own after this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.86,0:03:23.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I'm happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.50,0:03:27.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why don't we get some tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.18,0:03:27.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.09,0:03:36.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kureha-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.76,0:03:41.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? I wonder where it went?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.28,0:03:44.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It should be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.93,0:03:48.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.42,0:03:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The military almanac was here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.29,0:03:55.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata said she wanted to know more about Princess Iliya.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.58,0:04:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. If it's not there, then I don't know where it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.78,0:04:06.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we go to Naomi-san's place, there might be one.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.59,0:04:08.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll ask her about it next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.64,0:04:09.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.87,0:04:25.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Iliya was the eldest daughter of the current Archduke Arkadia.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.96,0:04:32.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you this before, but she was a super-famous tank commander.{tanker/tankman/whatever}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.04,0:04:36.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Earlier, Klaus-san also said "if only she were still alive" though...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.56,0:04:42.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She died. It was about two years ago, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.28,0:04:43.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the war?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.22,0:04:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The thing about Her Highness was, even though she was assigned to the Imperial Guard,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.35,0:04:55.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she also traveled all over the country so that she could enhance the national prestige.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.33,0:05:01.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then, on her way to a certain town, she tried to save a child who was drowning in a river and...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.22,0:05:08.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm a little relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.28,0:05:11.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is just a rumor, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.37,0:05:17.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iliya...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.54,0:05:19.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.30,0:05:22.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yumina-san and...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.26,0:05:24.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.79,0:05:37.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, it's Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.11,0:05:40.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.42,0:05:45.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yumina-san, uh, brought Yuuko-chan with her...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.49,0:05:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! Yuuko-chan is Martin-san's daughter...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.02,0:05:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is, there's an old lady named Jacott-san.{Jakotto according to credits, decide what you wanna do with it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.46,0:05:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jacott-san lives alone in the mountains and...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.34,0:06:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I also buy her vegetables at the morning market...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.36,0:06:06.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and you said the pickled vegetables from earlier were delicious, right?{Did she ever say this?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.07,0:06:09.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one who grew those vegetables was Jacott-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.57,0:06:15.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it seems that no one has seen Jacott-san lately...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.43,0:06:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She seemed to be in poor health, so we're worried about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.54,0:06:25.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She lives very deep inside the mountains, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.75,0:06:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine. I get it, I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.02,0:06:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll hear you out, so just wait a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.19,0:06:34.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.72,0:06:37.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Regarding Princess Iliya...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.28,0:06:41.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to improve relations with the Holy City of Rome,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.69,0:06:45.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it was rumored that she was going to marry the Emperor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.34,0:06:48.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if she did that, she'd have been the third queen!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.33,0:06:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The third! The THIRD!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.34,0:06:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's unbelievable, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.38,0:06:55.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, she would have just been a hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.57,0:07:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, when the princess died, any possibility of that ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.57,0:07:06.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And up until the salvation at the beginning of this year, we've done nothing but bicker with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.26,0:07:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good grief. We've finally arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.26,0:07:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A partially-constructed house?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.72,0:07:20.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't they say she lived alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.26,0:07:21.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I thought too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.73,0:07:32.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Madam!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.67,0:07:37.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. It was Yuuko?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.92,0:07:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.65,0:07:41.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's such a kind girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.68,0:07:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's too good for that snot-nosed Martin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.16,0:07:49.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is such a wonderful house.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.62,0:07:51.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.68,0:07:55.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You see, I'm the one who built this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.48,0:07:56.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.66,0:08:00.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what about the other one?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.81,0:08:04.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's for my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.03,0:08:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a son?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.61,0:08:10.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's in a distant city right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.87,0:08:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can come back when he wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.42,0:08:23.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I keep it clean so that whenever my son or that person returns, they may use it as they please.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.74,0:08:39.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When will your son and that person return, Madam?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.58,0:08:41.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very soon, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.35,0:08:44.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's coming soon is winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.08,0:08:47.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't it be best to leave the\Nmountain before it starts to snow?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.50,0:08:49.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.33,0:08:56.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is, I have to keep that house perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.84,0:09:01.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until then, I don't plan to die or leave this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.42,0:09:01.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.82,0:09:03.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get carried away by a joke!{Could be joking and getting carried away is bad, mmkay!}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.02,0:09:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are you going to prepare for winter?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.14,0:09:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Firewood?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.03,0:09:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Food?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.35,0:09:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't prepared at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.69,0:09:14.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One way or another, it will be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.07,0:09:18.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for worrying about me, young ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.12,0:09:20.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Madam!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.69,0:09:30.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What an obstinate old lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.24,0:09:35.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds just like you, that's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.33,0:09:38.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a break. How am I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.50,0:09:43.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because, Rio, you don't listen to what others say, and sometimes you're unruly, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.24,0:09:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.51,0:09:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, about that letter...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.33,0:09:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you show it to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.45,0:09:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you about last week's intelligence report, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.20,0:10:03.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the truth is, the Eastern Roman Army is on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.48,0:10:30.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so? For old lady Jacott?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.80,0:10:33.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, then bring these too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.00,0:10:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.50,0:10:40.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, do you know about what's happening at the peace meetings?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.57,0:10:42.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.33,0:10:43.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.88,0:10:46.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If only Princess Iliya were still alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.50,0:10:48.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, Martin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.24,0:10:53.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But didn't she have a younger sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.14,0:10:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,4,000,000 in change.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.59,0:10:56.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the first I've heard of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.16,0:11:01.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, she was from a different mother, although no one's sure of her whereabouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.11,0:11:05.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's third in line for the throne, or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.43,0:11:08.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, about that younger sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.59,0:11:16.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.99,0:11:18.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.58,0:11:20.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.13,0:11:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Want to take a walk for a bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.78,0:11:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.30,0:11:33.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of place was the village you were born in?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.93,0:11:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Normal for the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.06,0:11:41.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were fields, and lots of cows and goats.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.03,0:11:44.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there weren't that many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.28,0:11:47.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like here at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.40,0:11:50.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was a nice place, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.84,0:11:53.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And your parents raised you well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.66,0:11:55.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell by looking at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.82,0:11:59.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of place were you raised in?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.56,0:12:03.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.05,0:12:05.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't far from the capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.60,0:12:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were beautiful forests and lakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.41,0:12:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a small village.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.35,0:12:16.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I lived there with my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.84,0:12:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was also dull.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.75,0:12:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Days could go by where absolutely nothing happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.93,0:12:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what kept me from giving up...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.88,0:12:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was my favorite older sister.{it would be half-sister, rather than step-sister (minor spoiler for later in the ep). Plus, i don't think she says either...}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.98,0:12:34.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She would just come over and play occasionally,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.90,0:12:37.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I really admired her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.99,0:12:43.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was forgiving, kind, and solemnly resigned herself to her fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.41,0:12:46.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one I learned the trumpet from...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.57,0:12:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.08,0:12:49.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.17,0:12:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was also too kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.30,0:12:55.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because she was so kind, she lost her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.61,0:13:01.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I first came here, I thought this town was a maze.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.05,0:13:09.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I lost my way and ended up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.65,0:13:12.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the time, I thought that I had finally reached my goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.10,0:13:17.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I came to a realization later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.81,0:13:21.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This place was simply a dead end.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.41,0:13:25.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.57,0:13:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I tend to get lost a lot, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.37,0:13:34.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I like being lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.23,0:13:38.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it all right to get lost?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.99,0:13:40.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you reach a dead end?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.16,0:13:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.58,0:13:47.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how I met you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.50,0:13:57.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes I'm envious of you, Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.32,0:14:06.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If only I were as frank as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.03,0:14:27.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With this, we're all set.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.04,0:14:31.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so worried over someone like me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.02,0:14:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you remind me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.01,0:14:36.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...of my own mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.93,0:14:41.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember giving birth to a daughter as beautiful as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.00,0:14:45.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was born from an unforgivable love.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.72,0:14:51.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She always waited, once a year, for the man who may or may not come.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.93,0:14:57.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And in the midst of that misfortune, she passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.98,0:15:02.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you think that was misfortune?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.82,0:15:03.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.88,0:15:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm perfectly happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.06,0:15:08.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.02,0:15:12.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I promised that whenever that person came back,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.72,0:15:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd be here to welcome him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.54,0:15:17.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That promise is enough for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.98,0:15:18.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.08,0:15:24.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there anything else I could have done?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.06,0:15:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.44,0:15:29.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there was something I could have done, I would have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.88,0:15:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.97,0:15:34.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you fine with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.18,0:15:36.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really happy with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.96,0:15:40.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I have loving memories of him...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.81,0:15:46.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I have the hope that I can see him again once more...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.18,0:15:49.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's enough for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.37,0:15:51.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's more than enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.60,0:16:05.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's gotten this cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.12,0:16:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I first met you, it was snowing just like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.41,0:16:43.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Madam was young, Seize was a prosperous resort.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.69,0:17:05.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She fell in love with the son of a wealthy merchant.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.69,0:17:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then became pregnant with his child.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.30,0:17:19.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he was also already married.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.93,0:17:25.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By fortune or fate, his real wife was unable to bear any children.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.19,0:17:30.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that man took the boy she bore, and brought him back to his home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.39,0:17:37.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"One day, I will come back," was the promise he left her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.58,0:18:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even to this day, I still fantasize...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.64,0:18:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that if I had, at that time....
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.44,0:18:16.20,Alt,,0000,0000,0000,,Life is just filled...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.30,0:18:19.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...with nothing but continuous losses.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.98,0:18:16.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jacott-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.36,0:18:23.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you must have first gained in order to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.32,0:18:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a result, the more happiness you gain,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.13,0:18:30.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the greater the sorrow you'll feel when the time comes to lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.91,0:18:39.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's precisely the reminiscence of the happy times...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.85,0:18:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Precisely because they look back...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.96,0:18:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that people are able to continue living.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.94,0:18:54.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh right. Although it's probably not the best time right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.26,0:18:55.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.77,0:18:57.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a picture of Princess Iliya.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.37,0:18:58.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naomi-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.82,0:19:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Filicia, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.69,0:19:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This was taken about five years ago, when the Princess visited Seize.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.92,0:19:12.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Shuko?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.05,0:19:25.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rio-senpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.49,0:20:23.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is, my parents wanted me to find a good husband,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.54,0:20:28.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so that he could take over the family business.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.91,0:20:34.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when I heard the sound of that trumpet,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.91,0:20:38.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just couldn't forget about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.13,0:20:40.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That lady...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.41,0:20:43.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was Iliya-san, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.00,0:20:48.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it. You really did meet her before.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.40,0:20:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was beyond amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.67,0:20:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iliya's sound resounded within me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.02,0:20:58.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And because of that, you and I met.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.92,0:21:05.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably because I ran away to this small town.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.28,0:21:09.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why nothing mattered at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.61,0:21:13.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I always knew I was going to leave here someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.72,0:21:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But now, I really don't want to leave this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.71,0:21:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's all the more reason that I must.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.03,0:21:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.75,0:21:31.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's something only I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.17,0:21:39.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't plan on saying goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.66,0:21:46.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how far apart...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.79,0:21:50.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the sound will resound.{this matches what Iliya says in ep1, minus the "always"}{modified slightly. i think i will modify ep 1 slightly anyway}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.38,0:21:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because the sound resounds...{this continues what Iliya says in ep1, though the "because" doesn't come until Kanata's line end. Damn japanese.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.87,0:21:56.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...it will therefore... be conveyed.{This sounds sloppy here with the two of them saying it. A more literal might be / The sound resonates / therefore it will be conveyed.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.49,0:22:03.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kanata, have I been a worthy senpai up until now?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.55,0:22:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.{taking it back to ep1 still.}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.47,0:22:27.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, Rio-senpai left our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.97,0:22:33.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From now on... it will continue to resound in my heart.{lit inside my chest}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.79,0:22:38.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An intensely, and extremely wonderful sound of the sky that she gave me.{Both literal translations since I feel bad finagling these kinds of lines into non-Jap orders.}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.31,0:22:47.40,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Let’s remember our love and friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.31,0:22:47.40,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}aijou yuujou omoikasanete
Dialogue: 1,0:22:47.26,0:22:50.61,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}and play out their importance.
Dialogue: 1,0:22:47.26,0:22:50.61,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}taisetsu wo kanadeyou
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.52,0:23:08.53,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}We were so happy that we cried.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.52,0:23:08.53,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}ureshikute naita
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.51,0:23:14.53,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}It hurt so much that we laughed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.51,0:23:14.53,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}itakute waratta
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.59,0:23:23.73,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}But these are all proof that we are alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.59,0:23:23.73,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}dakedo sonna zenbu ga ikiteru akashi nan desu
Dialogue: 1,0:23:23.44,0:23:28.04,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Let’s move forward one step at a time.
Dialogue: 1,0:23:23.44,0:23:28.04,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}yukkuri aruite yukou
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.54,0:23:29.50,EDRE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Everybody singing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.41,0:23:34.01,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Let me hear the words of your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.41,0:23:34.01,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}hitosashi no honne kikasete
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.47,0:23:35.21,EDRE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}You’re just my friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.01,0:23:40.91,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Even if our love and friendship sometimes waver,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.01,0:23:40.91,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}aijou yuujou toki ni yuretemo
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.01,0:23:41.21,EDRE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}I know you know we’ll be happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.95,0:23:46.83,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}let’s make it echo forever and ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.95,0:23:46.83,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}zutto zutto hibiki aitai
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.95,0:23:47.19,EDRE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Can you count my precious hours?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.92,0:23:53.17,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Words are hardly enough to describe it.
Dialogue: 1,0:23:46.92,0:23:53.17,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}arifureteru kotoba de wa tsutaekirenai
Dialogue: 1,0:23:52.88,0:23:58.97,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}This is our harmony.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:52.88,0:23:58.97,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}watashitachi no harmony
Dialogue: 2,0:23:58.87,0:24:04.00,EDE,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}Can you hear it? Our harmony!
Dialogue: 3,0:23:58.87,0:24:04.00,EDR,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(240,300)}kikoeru our harmony
